title: The government is stepping up efforts to stop 'copycat' convicts refusing to appear in court, Justice Secretary Alex Chalk says
description: Alex Chalk said there was a 'real concern' that serious criminals would imitate previous notorious cases and refuse to come to the dock for sentencing.

title: Half a million jobless parents on benefits face up to 30 hours a week searching for work after overhaul by ministers
description: Half a million jobless parents on benefits will have to spend nearly twice as long looking for work, after an overhaul by ministers. Previously, parents could spend as little as 16 hours a week.

title: Florida mother, 33, is arrested after leaving her two-year-old child and eight-month-old baby alone in a car while she visited a bar
description: A Florida mom, 33, has been arrested after allegedly leaving her two-year-old and eight-month-old baby alone in a car while she went to a bar.

title: 'It shouldn't have taken three years to get this result': Tearful Team GB star Bianca Williams speaks out after two Met cops are sacked for lying about smelling drugs in stop and search of athlete boyfriend Ricardo Dos Santos
description: The Team GB world championship medallist, 29, and the Portuguese Olympian, 28, were pulled over and handcuffed as their then baby son, Zuri, was in the back of their car on July 4, 2020.

title: Unearthed: The lost memoir of Edward VIII that reveals the truth about him and Wallis Simpson... and how he was convinced he could marry her and be King
description: Long before Harry's tell-all tome, the Duke of Windsor poured out his heart to a ghostwriter. The result was an astonishing account in his own words of the affair that shocked the world.

title: Ugly moment IGA worker in Mandurah is hit and punched by a woman after he tried to check her bags as she left the store
description: Shocking footage has emerged of a woman striking a staff member at an IGA supermarket after he attempted to check her bag as she left the store.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Labour bigotry never far below the surface
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: More than 20 Labour councillors resigned over what they described as Keir Starmer's 'horrific and dehumanising rhetoric'. One accused him of condoning 'war crimes'.

title: Extraordinary footage resurfaces of Anthony Albanese at a pro-Palestine rally in Sydney
description: The decades-old grainy footage shows the future Prime Minister condemning the actions of the Israeli military at a protest at Martin Place in Sydney 's CBD.

title: Restaurants wage war on BOTS that gobble up prime-time reservations and then upsell them on third-party sites - forcing diners to fork out up to $340 to secure a spot at top bars
description: Owners of eateries like Carbone and Don Angie - the West Village sensation seen widely on TikTok - say it's an issue that largely began last summer, but has recently become more prevalent.

title: Ken Bruce's new station Greatest Hits Radio gains 800,000 listeners since June while Zoe Ball's BBC Breakfast Show loses 200,000, figures show
description: Ken Bruce admitted feeling like he had been 'taken for granted' when he left his longrunning Radio 2 show earlier this year.

title: Chilling moment assassin executes 'TikTok Narco Queen' Sabrina Duran, 24, in broad daylight in Chile
description: Sabrina Durán, a convicted drug dealer known as the 'TikTok Narco Queen,' was executed Santiago, Chile, on Tuesday.

title: Minister Robert Jenrick tells BBC boss Tim Davie the corporation has lost the confidence of the Jewish community over its Israel-Hamas war coverage in charged meeting in Parliament
description: BBC Director-General Tim Davie (pictured) faced hostile Tory MPs at a meeting of the 1922 committee following weeks of criticism over the BBC's using 'militants' to describe Hamas - and not terrorists.

title: Last surviving member of the RAF's heroic 'Guinea Pig Club', Polish WW2 veteran Jan Stangryciuk-Black, dies aged 101
description: Jan Stangryciuk-Black (pictured), who has died aged 101, a Polish veteran, was one of the airmen who underwent pioneering plastic surgery after suffering burn injuries in the Second World War.
